    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-baked-chicken-katsu-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> to a chopping board and cover with a sheet of <strong>cling film</strong></p><p>Bash the<strong> chicken</strong> <strong>breast</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until evenly flattened and approx. 1cm thickness</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-baked-chicken-katsu-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Crack your <strong>egg[s]</strong> into a shallow bowl and beat with a fork</p><p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> to another plate</p><p>Coat the <strong>flattened chicken</strong> in the flour, tap off the excess, then add them into the beaten egg and finally press them into the breadcrumbs firmly to evenly coat all over</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-baked-chicken-katsu-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>breaded chicken</strong> to a lightly oiled oven tray and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!) and crisp</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-baked-chicken-katsu-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is in the oven, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and grate your <strong>brown onion[s] </strong>and <strong>apple[s]</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-baked-chicken-katsu-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Add the <strong>grated onion</strong>, <strong>apple</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong> and <strong>carrot</strong> and cook for 3-4 min</p><p>Add your <strong>curry powder</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander</strong> and cook for a further 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the vegetables evenly</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-baked-chicken-katsu-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chicken stock</strong> and bring to a boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 5-7 min or until the sauce has thickened to a curry-like consistency \u2013 this is your <strong>katsu sauce</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Slice the <strong>cooked breaded chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-baked-chicken-katsu-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> sliced breaded chicken</strong> over the <strong>katsu sauce</strong> with the <strong>cooked rice</strong> and<strong> salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>salad</strong> with a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>sliced red chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
